Hi, I have added a few comments. When addressing the comments, please check if the things I mentioned are present somewhere else in your changes, I haven't gone through everything in detail yet.

You might also be interested in the [mathlib style guide](https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/style.html) if you haven't read it in detail yet. The style guide contains much information, but of course it can't codify every last detail of how mathlib code is supposed to look. The rest comes with experience of reading and wirking with mathlib.

We put a space after `/--` and before `-/`.
```suggestion
/-- A natural isomorphism between the functor `map (𝟭 C)` and `𝟭 (WithTerminal C)`. -/
```

We always use a single space for delimiting.
```suggestion
def mapId (C : Type*) [Category C] : map (𝟭 C) ≅ 𝟭 (WithTerminal C) where
```

Infix operators always get spaces around them:
```suggestion
/--A natural isomorphism between the functor `map (F ⋙ G) ` and `map F ⋙ map G `.-/
def mapComp {D : Type*} [Category D] {E : Type*} [Category E] (F : C ⥤ D) (G : D ⥤ E) :
```

We try to avoid `eqToHom` and `eqToIso` if possible, because they are difficult to work with. Almost always, it is possible to replace it with something that is better behaved. This is the case here. I would suggest the following definition:
```suggestion
def mapId (C : Type*) [Category C] : map (𝟭 C) ≅ 𝟭 (WithTerminal C) :=
  NatIso.ofComponents (fun X => match X with
    | of x => Iso.refl _
    | star => Iso.refl _) (by aesop_cat)
```

The `unfold` tactic is very rarely used in mathlib. We always prefer to have good API lemmas instead of unfolding a definition deep inside a proof. Luckily, these lemmas can be autogenerated by the `simps` attribute. I would suggest tagging `map`, `mapComp` and `map₂` with `@[simps]` (or `@[simps!]` if necessary), then the simplifier should be able to unfold the definition in the right places. If you get problems with match statements appearing in your goals, then you might need to add some lemmas by hand along the lines of
```lean
@[simp]
lemma mapId_hom_app_of (X : C) : (mapId C).hom.app (of X) = 𝟙 (of X) :=
  rfl
```
